- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as Markov decision processes are commonly used in AI for decision making and planning. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses lightweight approximative techniques for sampling from scheduler space, which involves algorithmic considerations. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper deals with concurrency optimisation problems, which are common in software engineering. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve programming language constructs and techniques for modelling and verifying Markov decision processes.
